# Transcribed from negation_flap.main.cpp: items {1,2,3}, blocker {2}, then
# two same-batch add+remove flaps of a blocker fact. Under the oracle's
# ingest-netting contract (StackSafeNegation.md §5.0/§5.5, provisional
# owner decision 3) BOTH flaps net to zero, so blocker(2) stays present and
# the final visible set is {1, 3}. This DIVERGES from the compiled golden,
# where the removal wins flap B's dequeue race and visible ends {1, 2, 3}.
batch
+ item 1
+ item 2
+ item 3
end
batch
+ blocker 2
end
# Flap A: add+remove of blocker(3), never previously present: nets to zero.
batch
+ blocker 3
- blocker 3
end
# Flap B: add+remove of blocker(2), which IS present: nets to zero (the
# documented divergence — today's engine removes it).
batch
+ blocker 2
- blocker 2
end
